Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.65,0:10:26.12,1080CN UP,,0,0,0,,字幕翻译给虫 记得点赞投币分享收藏关注转发
Dialogue: 1,0:00:00.17,0:00:04.20,1080CN,,0,0,0,,不少人认为火箭的垂直起飞垂直着陆(VTVL)技术
Dialogue: 2,0:00:00.17,0:00:04.20,1080EN,,0,0,0,,You may well be forgiven for thinking that Rockets which take off vertically
Dialogue: 1,0:00:04.25,0:00:09.85,1080CN,,0,0,0,,是太空叉和蓝源最近才出现的新技术，这无可厚非
Dialogue: 2,0:00:04.25,0:00:09.85,1080EN,,0,0,0,,and then land again vertically were a recent development by the likes of Blue Origin and SpaceX
Dialogue: 1,0:00:10.24,0:00:12.44,1080CN,,0,0,0,,但快速回首火箭发展史
Dialogue: 2,0:00:10.24,0:00:12.44,1080EN,,0,0,0,,But a quick look back into the history of rocketry
Dialogue: 1,0:00:12.44,0:00:18.81,1080CN,,0,0,0,,你会发现这项技术一点都不新奇，距离其首次使用已经有六十年之久
Dialogue: 2,0:00:12.44,0:00:18.81,1080EN,,0,0,0,,and you'll see that this technique is far from new and was first used nearly sixty years ago
Dialogue: 1,0:00:24.52,0:00:30.84,1080CN,,0,0,0,,让火箭VTVL需要很多技术的整合
Dialogue: 2,0:00:24.52,0:00:30.84,1080EN,,0,0,0,,Just to get a rocket to take off and land vertically requires a lot of technology to come together
Dialogue: 1,0:00:31.32,0:00:33.87,1080CN,,0,0,0,,首先你要有足够推力起飞
Dialogue: 2,0:00:31.32,0:00:33.87,1080EN,,0,0,0,,You need to have enough thrust to take off
Dialogue: 1,0:00:34.08,0:00:37.04,1080CN,,0,0,0,,还要有留有足够燃料返回地球
Dialogue: 2,0:00:34.08,0:00:37.04,1080EN,,0,0,0,,but then enough fuel left to descend back to earth
Dialogue: 1,0:00:37.44,0:00:45.08,1080CN,,0,0,0,,你还需要可重复启动的发动机，返回时还要承受高超音速的再入
Dialogue: 2,0:00:37.44,0:00:45.08,1080EN,,0,0,0,,you also need to be able to relight the engines and up to hypersonic speeds as the rocket falls back to the ground
Dialogue: 1,0:00:45.60,0:00:52.78,1080CN,,0,0,0,,你的发动机要能摇摆，从而控制返回时的姿态保证不失控
Dialogue: 2,0:00:45.60,0:00:52.78,1080EN,,0,0,0,,You need to be able to gimbal or tilt the engines and the Rockets angle of descent without it tumbling out of control
Dialogue: 1,0:00:53.24,0:00:58.81,1080CN,,0,0,0,,你的发动机还得有节流能力
Dialogue: 2,0:00:53.24,0:00:58.81,1080EN,,0,0,0,,You also need to be able to throttle down the engines to a small amount of thrust comparable
Dialogue: 1,0:00:58.89,0:01:02.54,1080CN,,0,0,0,,同一台发动机要节流到只有起飞推力的很小一部分
Dialogue: 2,0:00:58.89,0:01:02.54,1080EN,,0,0,0,,to that which is required to launch the rocket with the same engines
Dialogue: 1,0:01:02.81,0:01:07.90,1080CN,,0,0,0,,你还要有着陆腿，还要有伸缩着陆腿的机构
Dialogue: 2,0:01:02.81,0:01:07.90,1080EN,,0,0,0,,And you need legs to land on, and the mechanism of which to deploy them
Dialogue: 1,0:01:08.36,0:01:11.50,1080CN,,0,0,0,,像这种用尾翼当着陆腿的火箭
Dialogue: 2,0:01:08.36,0:01:11.50,1080EN,,0,0,0,,The image of rockets landing vertically on their tail fins
Dialogue: 1,0:01:11.50,0:01:15.23,1080CN,,0,0,0,,从上世纪三十年代以来人们就已经见得多了
Dialogue: 2,0:01:11.50,0:01:15.23,1080EN,,0,0,0,,has been popularized in science fiction since the early 1930s
Dialogue: 1,0:01:15.68,0:01:19.08,1080CN,,0,0,0,,尽管该技术真正实现花了将近三十年
Dialogue: 2,0:01:15.68,0:01:19.08,1080EN,,0,0,0,,though it took nearly 30 years to bring the technology to a point
Dialogue: 1,0:01:19.08,0:01:25.05,1080CN,,0,0,0,,这些技术基本上已经成熟，但应用的地方可能和你想的有点偏差
Dialogue: 2,0:01:19.08,0:01:25.05,1080EN,,0,0,0,,where it could be used practically though it wasn't quite in the way you might have expected
Dialogue: 1,0:01:25.60,0:01:30.36,1080CN,,0,0,0,,第一个以火箭为动力的VTVL
Dialogue: 2,0:01:25.60,0:01:30.36,1080EN,,0,0,0,,The first instance of a rocket-powered vertical takeoff and vertical landing
Dialogue: 1,0:01:30.57,0:01:34.27,1080CN,,0,0,135,,出现在1961年的Bell火箭腰带上
Dialogue: 2,0:01:30.57,0:01:34.27,1080EN,,0,0,100,,was shown in 1961 with the Bell Rocket Belt
Dialogue: 1,0:01:35.24,0:01:41.95,1080CN,,0,0,135,,尽管第一个火箭背包早在1919年就由毛子Alexander Andreyev发明并申请专利了
Dialogue: 2,0:01:35.24,0:01:41.95,1080EN,,0,0,100,,Although the first rocket pack had been developed and patented by a Russian Alexander Andreyev in 1919
Dialogue: 1,0:01:42.17,0:01:46.84,1080CN,,0,0,0,,之后还有不少人说自己发明出会飞的背包
Dialogue: 2,0:01:42.17,0:01:46.84,1080EN,,0,0,0,,and various people since have claimed to have invented things like the flying rucksack
Dialogue: 1,0:01:47.23,0:01:54.62,1080CN,,0,0,0,,但直到五十年代Bell航天系统才让他们的火箭腰带应用到美军
Dialogue: 2,0:01:47.23,0:01:54.62,1080EN,,0,0,0,,It wasn't until the mid-1950s that Bell AeroSystems starting work on the Bell Rocket Belt for the US Army
Dialogue: 1,0:01:55.00,0:01:58.38,1080CN,,0,0,0,,它使用过氧化氢发动机
Dialogue: 2,0:01:55.00,0:01:58.38,1080EN,,0,0,0,,The rocket belt used a hydrogen peroxide engine
Dialogue: 1,0:01:58.65,0:02:07.45,1080CN,,0,0,0,,但19升的燃料罐只够飞21秒，飞行120米的距离
Dialogue: 2,0:01:58.65,0:02:07.45,1080EN,,0,0,0,,but the 19 liters of fuel in the tanks could only provide 21 seconds of flight and travelled around about a 120 meters
Dialogue: 1,0:02:07.77,0:02:09.93,1080CN,,0,0,0,,但当公众看后惊了
Dialogue: 2,0:02:07.77,0:02:09.93,1080EN,,0,0,0,,But it was a hit with the public
Dialogue: 1,0:02:10.12,0:02:16.38,1080CN,,0,0,0,,不但来了个“全球巡演”，还出现在1965年詹姆斯·邦德的《007之霹雳弹》中
Dialogue: 2,0:02:10.12,0:02:16.38,1080EN,,0,0,0,,|and it was toured around the world and also appeared in the 1965 James Bond film Thunderball
Dialogue: 1,0:02:16.80,0:02:21.15,1080CN,,0,0,0,,但美军哪用得着“只能飞120米”的东西？所以就把合同取消了
Dialogue: 2,0:02:16.80,0:02:21.15,1080EN,,0,0,0,,But the US army were less impressed with the amount of backup required
Dialogue: 1,0:02:21.15,0:02:26.86,1080CN,,0,0,0,,但美军哪用得着“只能飞120米”的东西？所以就把合同取消了
Dialogue: 2,0:02:21.15,0:02:26.86,1080EN,,0,0,0,,to get one man 120 meters and they canceled the contract
Dialogue: 1,0:02:27.23,0:02:32.70,1080CN,,0,0,0,,但几年后，就出现了一个火箭动力、垂直着陆垂直起飞的载具
Dialogue: 2,0:02:27.23,0:02:32.70,1080EN,,0,0,0,,But within a few years there would be a rocket-powered vertical takeoff and vertical landing vehicle
Dialogue: 1,0:02:33.05,0:02:38.60,1080CN,,0,0,0,,全球数亿人都见证了它的成功
Dialogue: 2,0:02:33.05,0:02:38.60,1080EN,,0,0,0,,that would be a total success and be seen by hundreds of millions of people around the world
Dialogue: 1,0:02:39.05,0:02:41.79,1080CN,,0,0,0,,那就是阿波罗登月舱
Dialogue: 2,0:02:39.05,0:02:41.79,1080EN,,0,0,0,,That vehicle was the Apollo Lunar Lander
Dialogue: 1,0:02:42.04,0:02:47.36,1080CN,,0,0,0,,专门用于人类所去过的最不适宜居住的地方
Dialogue: 2,0:02:42.04,0:02:47.36,1080EN,,0,0,0,,a design that was used in the most inhospitable place man had ever been to
Dialogue: 1,0:02:47.52,0:02:50.81,1080CN,,0,0,0,,并且六次着陆无一失败
Dialogue: 2,0:02:47.52,0:02:50.81,1080EN,,0,0,0,,and worked without fail on six separate missions
Dialogue: 1,0:02:51.52,0:02:57.92,1080CN,,0,0,0,,虽然这个过程是反过来的(先垂直着陆再垂直起飞, VLVT)，它是先从月球轨道着陆
Dialogue: 2,0:02:51.52,0:02:57.92,1080EN,,0,0,0,,Though when you think about it it actually worked in reverse because it dropped from orbit to land on the moon
Dialogue: 1,0:02:58.24,0:03:04.09,1080CN,,0,0,0,,然后作为登月舱的部分——上升段起飞
Dialogue: 2,0:02:58.24,0:03:04.09,1080EN,,0,0,0,,and then the ascent module which was only part of a lunar lander took off to return the crew
Dialogue: 1,0:03:04.22,0:03:07.40,1080CN,,0,0,0,,送乘员返回指令舱，最后返回地球
Dialogue: 2,0:03:04.22,0:03:07.40,1080EN,,0,0,0,,back to the command module and then back onto earth
Dialogue: 1,0:03:08.03,0:03:14.57,1080CN,,0,0,135,,月球还有一个吼，就是重力只有地球的六分之一
Dialogue: 2,0:03:08.03,0:03:14.57,1080EN,,0,0,100,,There was also an advantage to landing on the moon because it only has one sixth of gravity of that on the Earth
Dialogue: 1,0:03:14.94,0:03:18.48,1080CN,,0,0,135,,对抗重力是火箭最大的难题
Dialogue: 2,0:03:14.94,0:03:18.48,1080EN,,0,0,100,,Fighting gravity is the biggest issue for any rocket
Dialogue: 1,0:03:18.91,0:03:23.97,1080CN,,0,0,0,,但登月舱下降发动机还要能够悬停并寻找落点
Dialogue: 2,0:03:18.91,0:03:23.97,1080EN,,0,0,0,,but particularly one which had to slow and hover to find a landing spot
Dialogue: 1,0:03:24.51,0:03:30.25,1080CN,,0,0,0,,虽然登月舱配有某些雷达可以自动检测离地高度
Dialogue: 2,0:03:24.51,0:03:30.25,1080EN,,0,0,0,,Although the lander had some automation in the form of radar to detect the distance from the ground
Dialogue: 1,0:03:30.41,0:03:33.12,1080CN,,0,0,0,,并有电脑控制唯一的一台发动机
Dialogue: 2,0:03:30.41,0:03:33.12,1080EN,,0,0,0,,and computer control of a single engine
Dialogue: 1,0:03:33.36,0:03:39.23,1080CN,,0,0,0,,当雷达本该在着陆最后阶段关闭却没关的时候
Dialogue: 2,0:03:33.36,0:03:39.23,1080EN,,0,0,0,,When the radar which should have been turned off for the final part of a descent was accidentally left on
Dialogue: 1,0:03:39.37,0:03:41.71,1080CN,,0,0,0,,它的大量数据过载了计算机
Dialogue: 2,0:03:39.37,0:03:41.71,1080EN,,0,0,0,,it overloaded the computer with data
Dialogue: 1,0:03:42.17,0:03:48.35,1080CN,,0,0,0,,计算机挂掉后，阿姆斯特朗只能手动控制登月舱着陆
Dialogue: 2,0:03:42.17,0:03:48.35,1080EN,,0,0,0,,Without the computer it fell to Neil Armstrong to manually land the lander on the surface of the Moon
Dialogue: 1,0:03:48.84,0:03:51.47,1080CN,,0,0,0,,阿姆斯特朗非常熟悉着陆的那一套理论
Dialogue: 2,0:03:48.84,0:03:51.47,1080EN,,0,0,0,,Armstrong was well versed with the procedure
Dialogue: 1,0:03:51.60,0:03:58.01,1080CN,,0,0,0,,他在地球版本的登月舱训练过——它有个亲切的名字叫会飞的床架
Dialogue: 2,0:03:51.60,0:03:58.01,1080EN,,0,0,0,,as he had trained on the Earth-based version of the lander which was affectionately known as the Flying Bedstead
Dialogue: 1,0:03:58.96,0:04:01.90,1080CN,,0,0,0,,在地球的重力下，且没有计算机的帮助
Dialogue: 2,0:03:58.96,0:04:01.90,1080EN,,0,0,0,,In Earth's gravity and with no computers to help him
Dialogue: 1,0:04:02.06,0:04:06.75,1080CN,,0,0,0,,他说控制那东西就像在扫帚棍上顶盘子一样
Dialogue: 2,0:04:02.06,0:04:06.75,1080EN,,0,0,0,,he described controlling it as like trying to balance a plate on the end of a broom handle
Dialogue: 1,0:04:07.07,0:04:13.24,1080CN,,0,0,0,,某次一个推进器没燃料了，他只有一秒的反应时间去弹出
Dialogue: 2,0:04:07.07,0:04:13.24,1080EN,,0,0,0,,and on one occasion when a thruster ran out of fuel he had just a second notice to eject
Dialogue: 1,0:04:13.47,0:04:17.82,1080CN,,0,0,0,,从鬼门关里走了一遭，而载具失控坠毁
Dialogue: 2,0:04:13.47,0:04:17.82,1080EN,,0,0,0,,and avoid almost certain death as the vehicle lost control and crashed
Dialogue: 1,0:04:18.48,0:04:22.49,1080CN,,0,0,0,,这告诉了我们，着陆这件事情有多难
Dialogue: 2,0:04:18.48,0:04:22.49,1080EN,,0,0,0,,This shows just how difficult it is to actually land something
Dialogue: 1,0:04:22.59,0:04:28.03,1080CN,,0,0,0,,尤其是用火箭发动机把一个又高又瘦的东西着陆
Dialogue: 2,0:04:22.59,0:04:28.03,1080EN,,0,0,0,,which is powered by rockets especially an object which is tall and thin
Dialogue: 1,0:04:28.06,0:04:33.18,1080CN,,0,0,0,,而且不是像登月舱那样VLVT，而是VTVL
Dialogue: 2,0:04:28.06,0:04:33.18,1080EN,,0,0,0,,and not really designed to come back in the reverse manner of how it took off
Dialogue: 1,0:04:33.80,0:04:41.02,1080CN,,0,0,135,,直到九十年代，才出现了真正的先垂直起飞再垂直着陆的火箭
Dialogue: 2,0:04:33.80,0:04:41.02,1080EN,,0,0,100,,It wasn't until the mid 1990s but the first true vertical takeoff and vertical landing rocket was seen
Dialogue: 1,0:04:41.18,0:04:45.79,1080CN,,0,0,135,,它就是麦道家的三角快帆-X——DC-X
Dialogue: 2,0:04:41.18,0:04:45.79,1080EN,,0,0,100,,in the form of the McDonnell Douglas Delta Clipper Experimental for DC-X
Dialogue: 1,0:04:46.46,0:04:51.92,1080CN,,0,0,135,,这个使用现成零件的更便宜的单级入轨(SSTO)载具的理念
Dialogue: 2,0:04:46.46,0:04:51.92,1080EN,,0,0,100,,The idea of a low-cost single-stage-to-orbit vehicle using off-the-shelf components
Dialogue: 1,0:04:52.14,0:04:59.40,1080CN,,0,0,135,,在1985年由麦道的前太空系统工程师Max Hunter提出
Dialogue: 2,0:04:52.14,0:04:59.40,1080EN,,0,0,100,,was proposed to McDonnell Douglas in 1985 by Max Hunter, their ex-chief engineer for Space Systems
Dialogue: 1,0:04:59.60,0:05:02.38,1080CN,,0,0,0,,此人从六十年代起就已经在构思这个概念
Dialogue: 2,0:04:59.60,0:05:02.38,1080EN,,0,0,0,,who had been thinking of the concept since the 60s
Dialogue: 1,0:05:02.64,0:05:06.94,1080CN,,0,0,0,,但麦道本身对此理念并没有太大兴趣
Dialogue: 2,0:05:02.64,0:05:06.94,1080EN,,0,0,0,,but Mcdonnell Douglas weren't interested in funding the idea themselves
Dialogue: 1,0:05:07.23,0:05:14.03,1080CN,,0,0,0,,所以同样还为里根总统的战略防御计划组织工作的Hunter
Dialogue: 2,0:05:07.23,0:05:14.03,1080EN,,0,0,0,,So Hunter who had also worked for President Ronald Reagan's Strategic Defense Initiative Organization or SDIO
Dialogue: 1,0:05:14.16,0:05:20.72,1080CN,,0,0,0,,与Jerry Pournelle、Graham将军一起游说副总统Dan Quayle
Dialogue: 2,0:05:14.16,0:05:20.72,1080EN,,0,0,0,,went with Jerry Pournelle and General Graham to sell the idea to Vice President Dan Quayle
Dialogue: 1,0:05:20.92,0:05:26.40,1080CN,,0,0,0,,他们假设任何基于太空的防御系统一定需要一个运输系统
Dialogue: 2,0:05:20.92,0:05:26.40,1080EN,,0,0,0,,on the premise that any space-based defense system would need a delivery system
Dialogue: 1,0:05:26.56,0:05:32.57,1080CN,,0,0,0,,该系统要非常便宜、可靠，比航天飞机复用速度快
Dialogue: 2,0:05:26.56,0:05:32.57,1080EN,,0,0,0,,that would be far cheaper, more reliable, and with much faster turnaround times than the space shuttle
Dialogue: 1,0:05:33.20,0:05:37.31,1080CN,,0,0,0,,项目通过，还扛着SDIO的大旗
Dialogue: 2,0:05:33.20,0:05:37.31,1080EN,,0,0,0,,With the approval of a project and it coming under the SDIO banner
Dialogue: 1,0:05:37.39,0:05:40.36,1080CN,,0,0,0,,该项目直接撇开NASA和空军那边不管
Dialogue: 2,0:05:37.39,0:05:40.36,1080EN,,0,0,0,,away from the bureaucracy of NASA and the Air Force
Dialogue: 1,0:05:40.67,0:05:44.51,1080CN,,0,0,0,,直接在麦道组了一百来人的团队
Dialogue: 2,0:05:40.67,0:05:44.51,1080EN,,0,0,0,,it allowed the small team of around a hundred people at McDonnell Douglas
Dialogue: 1,0:05:44.81,0:05:54.11,1080CN,,0,0,0,,从1991年开始，在21个月里造了一个三分之一缩尺模型原型机，造价仅六千万
Dialogue: 2,0:05:44.81,0:05:54.11,1080EN,,0,0,0,,to build a one-third scale prototype in just 21 months for a cost of just $60 million dollars starting in 1991
Dialogue: 1,0:05:54.76,0:06:01.04,1080CN,,0,0,0,,该设计让火箭像往常一样垂直起飞，然后垂直着陆回原来的位置
Dialogue: 2,0:05:54.76,0:06:01.04,1080EN,,0,0,0,,The design would take off like a normal rocket and then land back again in the same vertical position
Dialogue: 1,0:06:01.16,0:06:07.18,1080CN,,0,0,0,,不使用降落伞，使用和起飞相同的发动机，着陆在伸出的着陆腿上
Dialogue: 2,0:06:01.16,0:06:07.18,1080EN,,0,0,0,,as it took off on extendable legs under its own power and without any parachutes
Dialogue: 1,0:06:07.71,0:06:14.06,1080CN,,0,0,0,,原型机设计上就是无法入轨的，实际上最高也只飞到2.5千米
Dialogue: 2,0:06:07.71,0:06:14.06,1080EN,,0,0,0,,The prototype was never designed to go into orbit and in fact only of a flew to a height of around 2.5 km
Dialogue: 1,0:06:14.25,0:06:16.30,1080CN,,0,0,0,,但也够验证这一理念了
Dialogue: 2,0:06:14.25,0:06:16.30,1080EN,,0,0,0,,but that was enough to prove the concept
Dialogue: 1,0:06:16.68,0:06:19.95,1080CN,,0,0,0,,外壳使用复合材料按缩尺比定制
Dialogue: 2,0:06:16.68,0:06:19.95,1080EN,,0,0,0,,The outer shell was custom-built by Scale Composites
Dialogue: 1,0:06:20.14,0:06:26.73,1080CN,,0,0,0,,剩余部分比如RL-10A发动机、控制系统都是现成的组件
Dialogue: 2,0:06:20.14,0:06:26.73,1080EN,,0,0,0,,and the rest of a craft including the RL-10A engines and the control systems were off-the-shelf components
Dialogue: 1,0:06:27.10,0:06:31.82,1080CN,,0,0,0,,测试从1993年开始，其间进行三次试飞
Dialogue: 2,0:06:27.10,0:06:31.82,1080EN,,0,0,0,,The testing program started in 1993 and flew three test flights
Dialogue: 1,0:06:31.82,0:06:36.25,1080CN,,0,0,0,,直到战略防卫计划结束，资金耗尽
Dialogue: 2,0:06:31.82,0:06:36.25,1080EN,,0,0,0,,until funding ran out as a result of the SDI program coming to an end
Dialogue: 1,0:06:36.62,0:06:40.12,1080CN,,0,0,0,,NASA后来补了点钱，测试继续
Dialogue: 2,0:06:36.62,0:06:40.12,1080EN,,0,0,0,,NASA provided further funding and testing resumed
Dialogue: 1,0:06:40.80,0:06:46.96,1080CN,,0,0,0,,一次飞行中，DC-X发生一次小型爆炸，侧面炸出一个可见的洞
Dialogue: 2,0:06:40.80,0:06:46.96,1080EN,,0,0,0,,On one flight a minor explosion occurred and the DC-X can be seen with a hole in its side
Dialogue: 1,0:06:47.26,0:06:50.99,1080CN,,0,0,0,,但它成功执行终止程序并自动降落
Dialogue: 2,0:06:47.26,0:06:50.99,1080EN,,0,0,0,,but it successfully performed an abort and an auto landing
Dialogue: 1,0:06:51.48,0:06:55.71,1080CN,,0,0,0,,修复后在1995年继续进行测试
Dialogue: 2,0:06:51.48,0:06:55.71,1080EN,,0,0,0,,After the repairs it continued testing in 1995
Dialogue: 1,0:06:55.96,0:07:01.04,1080CN,,0,0,0,,但后来一次重着陆，摔裂了外壳，资金又断了
Dialogue: 2,0:06:55.96,0:07:01.04,1080EN,,0,0,0,,But after a hard landing cracked the outer shell and again funding had been cut
Dialogue: 1,0:07:01.29,0:07:04.06,1080CN,,0,0,0,,坏的地方没钱修
Dialogue: 2,0:07:01.29,0:07:04.06,1080EN,,0,0,0,,there was not enough funds to carry out repairs
Dialogue: 1,0:07:04.57,0:07:11.96,1080CN,,0,0,0,,好说歹说NASA在1995年接手了项目，毕竟它之前飞行还是挺成功的
Dialogue: 2,0:07:04.57,0:07:11.96,1080EN,,0,0,0,,During 1995 NASA begrudgingly agreed to take on the project because of its previous test flight successes
Dialogue: 1,0:07:12.48,0:07:17.55,1080CN,,0,0,0,,但经过几次升级后，项目改名DC-XA
Dialogue: 2,0:07:12.48,0:07:17.55,1080EN,,0,0,0,,But with several upgrades and the project would be renamed as the DC-XA
Dialogue: 1,0:07:18.01,0:07:23.24,1080CN,,0,0,135,,在1996年测试继续，不过这次它有了一个对手
Dialogue: 2,0:07:18.01,0:07:23.24,1080EN,,0,0,100,,In 1996 testing resumed but this time it was also in competition
Dialogue: 1,0:07:23.55,0:07:26.91,1080CN,,0,0,135,,那就是洛克希德马丁的X-33冒险之星项目
Dialogue: 2,0:07:23.55,0:07:26.91,1080EN,,0,0,100,,with the Lockheed Martin X-33 Venture Star Project
Dialogue: 1,0:07:27.12,0:07:31.34,1080CN,,0,0,0,,NASA将该项目作为替代航天飞机的选择之一
Dialogue: 2,0:07:27.12,0:07:31.34,1080EN,,0,0,0,,which NASA had chosen as a possible replacement for the Shuttle
Dialogue: 1,0:07:31.71,0:07:37.40,1080CN,,0,0,0,,最终DC-X输了，按NASA的解释，原因是“资金短缺”
Dialogue: 2,0:07:31.71,0:07:37.40,1080EN,,0,0,0,,And ultimately the DC-X lost out to what NASA said were budgetary constraints
Dialogue: 1,0:07:37.60,0:07:43.84,1080CN,,0,0,0,,但更根本原因是X-33才是亲儿子项目，NASA单纯想钦点DC-X项目下马罢了
Dialogue: 2,0:07:37.60,0:07:43.84,1080EN,,0,0,0,,but too many the X-33 was NASA's pet project and the DC-X was something they didn't really want
Dialogue: 1,0:07:44.12,0:07:49.15,1080CN,,0,0,0,,即使造一个新的DC-XA只要五千万
Dialogue: 2,0:07:44.12,0:07:49.15,1080EN,,0,0,0,,Even though the cost of building a new DC-XA was just $50 million
Dialogue: 1,0:07:49.29,0:07:52.94,1080CN,,0,0,0,,和别的火箭想比还是挺便宜的
Dialogue: 2,0:07:49.29,0:07:52.94,1080EN,,0,0,0,,a very cheap price when compared to other rocket projects
Dialogue: 1,0:07:53.28,0:07:59.61,1080CN,,0,0,0,,NASA之后几年又在X-33项目上花了9.2个亿
Dialogue: 2,0:07:53.28,0:07:59.61,1080EN,,0,0,0,,NASA would go on to spend $920M on the X-33 over the next few years
Dialogue: 1,0:07:59.88,0:08:05.10,1080CN,,0,0,0,,最后复合材料油箱整不明白，项目还是取消了
Dialogue: 2,0:07:59.88,0:08:05.10,1080EN,,0,0,0,,only to cancel it at the last minute due to technical issues with the composite fuel tanks
Dialogue: 1,0:08:05.39,0:08:08.49,1080CN,,0,0,0,,并且这玩意一次都没飞起来过
Dialogue: 2,0:08:05.39,0:08:08.49,1080EN,,0,0,0,,and before any test flights had taken place
Dialogue: 1,0:08:09.15,0:08:14.35,1080CN,,0,0,0,,尽管DC-X挂了，但它鼓励了蓝源的新薛帕德火箭
Dialogue: 2,0:08:09.15,0:08:14.35,1080EN,,0,0,0,,Although the DC-X was at an end, it inspired the Blue Origin New Shepard
Dialogue: 1,0:08:14.52,0:08:20.36,1080CN,,0,0,0,,当年参与DC-X项目的一些工程师也被蓝源挖去
Dialogue: 2,0:08:14.52,0:08:20.36,1080EN,,0,0,0,,and some of the engineers which worked on the DC-X project went on to work at Blue Origin
Dialogue: 1,0:08:20.84,0:08:27.64,1080CN,,0,0,0,,太空叉就一句话也不说，我们也能在猎鹰九号上看到很多DC-X的影子
Dialogue: 2,0:08:20.84,0:08:27.64,1080EN,,0,0,0,,Although SpaceX won't say directly we can see the influence of the DC-X on the Falcon 9 reusable rockets too
Dialogue: 1,0:08:28.24,0:08:31.82,1080CN,,0,0,135,,一些NASA的工程师也相信利用DC-X的理念
Dialogue: 2,0:08:28.24,0:08:31.82,1080EN,,0,0,100,,Some NASA engineers also believe that DC-X concept
Dialogue: 1,0:08:31.84,0:08:36.49,1080CN,,0,0,135,,可以制造出最多可载六人的火星着陆器
Dialogue: 2,0:08:31.84,0:08:36.49,1080EN,,0,0,100,,would make a good Mars Lander with a crew of up to six people
Dialogue: 1,0:08:36.94,0:08:42.01,1080CN,,0,0,135,,在地球上的测试证明其到了弱重力的火星是可行的
Dialogue: 2,0:08:36.94,0:08:42.01,1080EN,,0,0,100,,The testing on earth proved that it could be done and with the weaker gravity of Mars
Dialogue: 1,0:08:42.12,0:08:45.07,1080CN,,0,0,0,,运力可以得到极大提升
Dialogue: 2,0:08:42.12,0:08:45.07,1080EN,,0,0,0,,the payload capacity would be greatly enhanced
Dialogue: 1,0:08:45.45,0:08:52.60,1080CN,,0,0,0,,所以我们今天看到太空叉和蓝源都用的和DC-X类似的技术
Dialogue: 2,0:08:45.45,0:08:52.60,1080EN,,0,0,0,,And so we come to the present day with both SpaceX and Blue Origen, both using similar techniques to the DC-X
Dialogue: 1,0:08:52.92,0:08:58.86,1080CN,,0,0,0,,虽然DC-X项目的取消留给了他们足够的时间追赶，但设计出人意料的快
Dialogue: 2,0:08:52.92,0:08:58.86,1080EN,,0,0,0,,Though with the benefit of the extra time since the demise of the DC-X, the designs have moved on considerably
Dialogue: 1,0:08:59.12,0:09:06.28,1080CN,,0,0,0,,猎鹰九号很快就证明了它可以运送商业载荷和军用载荷入轨
Dialogue: 2,0:08:59.12,0:09:06.28,1080EN,,0,0,0,,with the SpaceX Falcon 9 proving that it can be used for delivering commercial and military payloads into orbit
Dialogue: 1,0:09:06.64,0:09:09.20,1080CN,,0,0,0,,甚至还能送一辆车去火星
Dialogue: 2,0:09:06.64,0:09:09.20,1080EN,,0,0,0,,and even sending a car to Mars
Dialogue: 1,0:09:09.76,0:09:14.00,1080CN,,0,0,0,,他们说站在巨人的肩膀上就没啥新东西可学了
Dialogue: 2,0:09:09.76,0:09:14.00,1080EN,,0,0,0,,They say that there is nothing new and that we stand on the shoulders of giants
Dialogue: 1,0:09:14.00,0:09:15.58,1080CN,,0,0,0,,这话倒也没错
Dialogue: 2,0:09:14.00,0:09:15.58,1080EN,,0,0,0,,and that's pretty much true
Dialogue: 1,0:09:15.85,0:09:22.78,1080CN,,0,0,0,,但每一步都需要有才能者了解前人的成果，才能创造新的东西
Dialogue: 2,0:09:15.85,0:09:22.78,1080EN,,0,0,0,,But each step of a way needs skilled people to fully understand what has gone before in order to build the new ideas
Dialogue: 1,0:09:23.36,0:09:29.10,1080CN,,0,0,0,,就像DC-X验证了垂直起飞、空中机动和垂直着陆的方法一样
Dialogue: 2,0:09:23.36,0:09:29.10,1080EN,,0,0,0,,Just as the DC-X proved a principle of vertical takeoff in air maneuvering and vertical landing
Dialogue: 1,0:09:29.34,0:09:34.88,1080CN,,0,0,135,,太空叉参考了那些方法，还找到了新的实现方法并应用之
Dialogue: 2,0:09:29.34,0:09:34.88,1080EN,,0,0,100,,SpaceX have taken those principles and found new solutions to enable them
Dialogue: 1,0:09:34.97,0:09:38.81,1080CN,,0,0,135,,创造了完全可商用的可回收火箭运载系统
Dialogue: 2,0:09:34.97,0:09:38.81,1080EN,,0,0,100,,to make a fully working reusable rocket delivery system
Dialogue: 1,0:09:38.91,0:09:43.50,1080CN,,0,0,0,,而这些成就还会鼓励有才能者继续迈出下一步
Dialogue: 2,0:09:38.91,0:09:43.50,1080EN,,0,0,0,,and that takes people that have the skills to make those next steps
